INTRODUCTION: During adrenal venous sampling (AVS) procedure, radiologists 
administer a contrast agent via the catheter to visualize the proper catheter 
position.
MATERIALS AND METHODS: A patient with primary aldosteronism 
diagnostic-hypothesis was admitted for AVS. A venogram was performed to confirm 
